snippet.textDisplay: "Oh you cures ills with the breath of Jesus"-- this echoes the greatness of those rasools who emerged from the House of Abraham. Not just a naat but an intense tribute to the the "untaught servant" who descended from the outcast tribe of Ismael.  Phenomenal.  I certainly hope that Atif Aslam's direction in life was altered by his rendition of this tribute. Yes, he needs to make a living, but after this, the Creator can only be pleased....

snippet.textDisplay:
From an Indian Hindu , 
The reason why this naat crossed 100 million views, listening to this gives eternal peace and calmness to your mind and soul,
Yesterday I was highly disturbed by observing hatred and abusive interactions among indo-pak people at social sites..
But after listening to this and atif sir's magical voice... I have forgotten everything. What a beautiful naat.
Respect to each individual on this earth, we should spread love and peace. May God/Allah /bhagwan bless everyone on this earth. Indians and Pakistanis should love and respect each other. As we all are humans first and creation of almighty.
